**********************************************************************
MAUI aloha demo code
**********************************************************************
What this demo does:
  - "Aloha MAUI demo..." is displayed.
  - "Press a key to exit" is displayed.
  - When a key on the input device is selected, the program exits.

**********************************************************************
System requirements:
  - A working MAUI environment is assumed.
  - The demo requires that gfx is in memory.
  - The demo requires that mfm is in memory.
 
*********************************************************************
Directories: 
  - Source code 
      $MWOS/SRC/MAUI/DEMOS/ALOHA

  - Assets
      $MWOS/<operating system>/<hardware platform>/ASSETS/FONTS

*********************************************************************
To make this demo:
  - From the source file directory type:
      % os9make

*********************************************************************
Operation:
  - To list the options available for this demo type the demo name 
	followed by -? or -h.

  - The font 'default.fnt' must be in memory. The font can be found
	  in the assets directory noted above.

  - The process 'maui_inp' must be running in the background. To 
	verify that it is use the os9000 command 'procs'. If it is not 
	present run it before starting the demo. e.g.

	  $ maui_inp <>>>/nil &

*********************************************************************

